- cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper deals with the problem of revenue maximization in the context of allocating goods to buyers, which is a classic problem in game theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents approximation algorithms for the revenue maximization problem, which involves designing efficient algorithms and data structures. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with the problem of allocating goods to buyers in an envy-free manner, which is a common problem in AI and multi-agent systems. 
- cs.EC (Economics and Computation): The paper deals with the problem of revenue maximization in the context of allocating goods to buyers, which is a classic problem in the intersection of economics and computation. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the computational complexity of the revenue maximization problem and proves lower bounds on the approximability of the problem, which is a topic in computational complexity theory.
